When exporting issues via JSON exporter, we will get user details at the end of the JSON data. The data should look something like below:
{noformat}
"users" : [ {
    "name" : "support",
    "fullname" : "support",
    "email" : "support@mail.com",
    "groups" : [ "jira-users", "jira-developers" ],
    "active" : true
  }, {
    "name" : "user",
    "fullname" : "user",
    "email" : "user@mail.com",
    "groups" : [ "jira-users" ],
    "active" : true
  }, {
    "name" : "admin",
    "fullname" : "admin",
    "email" : "admin@mail.com",
    "groups" : [ "jira-users", "jira-administrators", "jira-developers" ],
    "active" : true
  }
{noformat}

Notice that there's the "active" attribute inside the JSON data. All of the users are stated as active, while actually there are some user that is made inactive from User Browser. Hence, the expected output should be "active": false instead of "active":true.

